---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="writing -- alexander campos" description="Technical writing on identity modeling, system design, and local intelligence.">
  <article>
    <h1>Writing</h1>

    <p>
      I think by writing. Most of these are in progress.
      When ready, they'll live on
      <a href="https://substack.com/@alexinthefield">Substack</a>.
    </p>

    <dl class="writing-list">
      <div class="writing-entry">
        <dt><a href="/writing/on-observation-and-identity-modeling">On Observation and Identity Modeling</a></dt>
        <dd class="date">2026</dd>
        <dd>
          How systems build models of the people who use them — and what happens
          when the model starts shaping the person. Built from observations
          during Guardian and Reframed development.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div class="writing-entry">
        <dt><a href="/writing/where-the-difference-is-stored">On Observation and Identity Modeling, Part II</a></dt>
        <dd class="date">2026</dd>
        <dd>
          Where the loop became measurable. The mechanism turned out to be the same
          in three different kinds of system — and the only question that's left is
          what each of us puts on the other side of it.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div class="writing-entry">
        <dt>On Reframe Detection</dt>
        <dd class="date">in progress</dd>
        <dd>
          How language models subtly reshape user intent through seven classification types,
          and the engineering challenge of detecting it in real-time. Built from observations
          during Guardian development.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div class="writing-entry">
        <dt>Memory Compression as Forgetting Curve</dt>
        <dd class="date">in progress</dd>
        <dd>
          Technical walkthrough of the 4-level hierarchical memory pipeline
          (raw -> summary -> pattern -> principle), why strength decay mirrors human consolidation,
          and what retrieval reinforcement means for AI systems that accumulate context over months.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div class="writing-entry">
        <dt>Ownership at Every Scale</dt>
        <dd class="date">in progress</dd>
        <dd>
          The unifying thesis behind ForgeFrame and Guardian: every interaction with an
          intelligence system is an opportunity for extraction or preservation. The same
          primitive applies at every scale.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    console.log(
      '%c the writing is the thinking made visible. ',
      'color: #E8DCC8; font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px;'
    );
  </script>
</Page>

<style>
  .writing-list {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .writing-entry {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--white-08);
  }

  .writing-entry:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  dt {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  dt {
    color: var(--glow-hot);
  }

  .date {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--white-45);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  dd:not(.date) {
    color: var(--glow);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
